Hi. I am a reader of omniscient reader living in Korea.
There are a lot of great things about this work, but I'll talk a little bit for those of you who read it early.

Because of the pronunciation of Chinese and Korean, kimdokja has a triple meaning.

dokja indirectly expresses the person who has read the novel and the person who leads it in a word as a reader and a leader.

In the last Korean and Chinese characters, dokja means a lonely person.

I will only explain it so far. Please try it.
